The paper discusses the use of Twitter as a data source for altmetrics in scholarly communication, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, retrieval, and dissemination of digital information. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers the analysis of social media data, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the search and ranking of information, cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), which covers the study of social phenomena, and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), which deals with the protection of digital information.
